13.02	Brad_McCrimmon	Brad McCrimmon	Byron Brad McCrimmon (March 29, 1959 â€“ September 7, 2011) from Plenty, Saskatchewan, was a Canadian professional ice hockey player and coach. McCrimmon played 18 seasons in the National Hockey League (NHL) between 1979 and 1997. From 1997 to his death, he was a coach, ultimately with Lokomotiv Yaroslavl of the Kontinental Hockey League. On September 7, 2011, McCrimmon died along with all of the Lokomotiv team, when the flight carrying the team crashed in Yaroslavl, Russia.	
